(1127, 1, '2013-04-23 21:37:46', '2013-04-23 21:37:46', '<h3 class="fizzics"><strong>Here is how it works</strong></h3><img src="http://www.foodwecook.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/howitworks-2.jpg" alt="howitworks-2" width="700" height="465" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-990" />\r\n\r\n<div class="fizzics">\r\n<p><strong>FUN FACT</strong> - You may not realize it, but there''s more to the root beer float than just the sweet taste. The tiny bubbles of air present in the soda cause the ice cream to float and are nucleation sites for the formation of large bubbles of carbon dioxide.\r\n</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<br/>\r\n\r\n<div class="internal get_fizz_button" id="fizzics_CTA">\r\n<a href="#store">Try it Now!</a>\r\n</div>', 'Fizzics', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '389-revision-26', '', '', '2013-04-23 21:37:46', '2013-04-23 21:37:46', '', 389, 'http://www.foodwecook.com/389-revision-26/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
